n">The Justice Department is investigating a series of oil market trades that right before important moves related to the war with Iran. At least four trades worth $2.6 billion are being examined. NBC News’ Allie Canal explains the timing of the bets.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778190659503_now_hallie_aca_oil_trades_260507.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778190659503_now_hallie_aca_oil_trades_260507.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778190659503_now_hallie_aca_oil_trades_260507_S3_1920x1080-pv4d4q.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 21:51:05 GMT</pubDate><title>Source: DOJ investigating suspicious oil trades timed around Iran war</title><updateDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 21:51:39 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Abigail Williams</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Colin Sheeley</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 07 May 2026 21:04:35 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The U.S. is urging the government to break with Tehran-backed militia groups following more than 600 attacks against U.S. diplomatic facilities. </description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/national-security/iran-backed-groups-targeted-us-facilities-iraq-600-us-official-says-rcna344062</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/national-security/iran-backed-groups-targeted-us-facilities-iraq-600-us-official-says-rcna344062</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260318-baghdad-us-embassy-mn-1335-0d8d8a-7240cc.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1000" width="1500"><media:credit>Hadi Mizban</media:credit><media:text type="plain">An Iraqi army armored humvee vehicle is deployed to protect the U.S. Embassy in Baghdad</media:text><media:description type="plain">An Iraqi army armored vehicle is deployed near the banks of the Tigris River to protect the U.S. Embassy fortified &#34;Green Zone&#34; in Baghdad on March 14.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-baghdad-us-embassy-mn-1335-554af3.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1200" width="1800"><media:credit>Ahmad Al-Rubaye </media:credit><media:text type="plain">A fire burns outside the grounds of the U.S. Embassy in Baghdad</media:text><media:description type="plain">An Iraqi army armored vehicle is deployed near the banks of the Tigris River to protect the U.S. Embassy fortified &#34;Green Zone&#34; in Baghdad on March 14.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260318-baghdad-us-embassy-mn-1335-0d8d8a-7240cc.jpg" height="1000" width="1500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 21:04:35 GMT</pubDate><title>Iran-backed groups targeted U.S. facilities in Iraq 600 times, U.S. official says</title><updateDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 21:04:35 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Alexander Smith</dc:creator><dc:contributor>The Associated Press</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 08 May 2026 07:38:32 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Early results Friday from nationwide elections in Britain suggested a historic drubbing for Prime Minister Keir Starmer’s Labour Party and sweeping gains for hard-right Reform U.K., led by Trump ally Nigel Farage.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/united-kingdom/starmer-labour-reform-farage-uk-election-rcna344013</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/united-kingdom/starmer-labour-reform-farage-uk-election-rcna344013</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260508-starmer-rs-6e118f.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Justin Tallis</media:credit><media:text type="plain">TOPSHOT-BRITAIN-POLITICS-VOTE</media:text><media:description type="plain">Starmer will now face increasing doubts over his future amid widespread speculation his colleagues may move against him.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260508-farage-rs-fc7b1a.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Chris Radburn</media:credit><media:text type="plain">TOPSHOT-BRITAIN-POLITICS-VOTE</media:text><media:description type="plain">Starmer will now face increasing doubts over his future amid widespread speculation his colleagues may move against him.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260508-green-rs-ce16a9.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1666" width="2500"><media:credit>Jon Rowley</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Wales Green Party Leader Anthony Slaughter Votes In The 2026 Senedd Election</media:text><media:description type="plain">Starmer will now face increasing doubts over his future amid widespread speculation his colleagues may move against him.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260508-starmer-rs-6e118f.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 07:38:32 GMT</pubDate><title>Hard-right Reform routs Starmer’s Labour in U.K. elections as Trump ally Farage hails ‘historic shift’</title><updateDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 08:52:19 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Steve Kopack</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 08 May 2026 09:00:00 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The April jobs coming Friday morning is expected to show a resilient U.S. labor market despite the global energy shock from the U.S. war with Iran.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/business/economy/april-jobs-report-iran-war-pressure-rcna344166</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/business/economy/april-jobs-report-iran-war-pressure-rcna344166</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-03/260305-now-hiring-sign-ch-1554-705b33.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Joe Raedle</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Now Hiring sign.</media:text><media:description type="plain">The consensus among economists is that Friday&#39;s jobs report will show the U.S. added positions in April; but not everyone is that optimistic. </media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-03/260305-now-hiring-sign-ch-1554-705b33.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 09:00:00 GMT</pubDate><title>April jobs report expected to show gains despite Iran war pressure</title><updateDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 09:00:00 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 07 May 2026 23:13:20 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Five states - Texas, Georgia, Virginia, Arizona, and California - confirm passengers who had left the cruise ship before the Hantavirus outbreak was known about, are back home. None are showing symptoms. NBC News’ Camila Bernal reports on what steps are being taken to mitigate the risk of any spread of the virus.</description><expires>2056-05-07T23:10:30.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">nn_cbe_passengershantaviruscruiseshipus_260507</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/nightly-news/video/multiple-passengers-from-cruise-ship-back-in-u-s-262949957581</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nn_cbe_passengershantaviruscruiseshipus_260507/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>Multiple passengers from cruise ship back in U.S.</media:title><media:player url="https://www.nbcnews.com/nightly-news/video/multiple-passengers-from-cruise-ship-back-in-u-s-262949957581"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778195421931_nn_cbe_passengershantaviruscruiseshipus_260507_S3_1920x1080-j6ys8e.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">Five states - Texas, Georgia, Virginia, Arizona, and California - confirm passengers who had left the cruise ship before the Hantavirus outbreak was known about, are back home. None are showing symptoms. NBC News’ Camila Bernal reports on what steps are being taken to mitigate the risk of any spread of the virus.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778195421931_nn_cbe_passengershantaviruscruiseshipus_260507.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778195421931_nn_cbe_passengershantaviruscruiseshipus_260507.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778195421931_nn_cbe_passengershantaviruscruiseshipus_260507_S3_1920x1080-j6ys8e.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 23:10:28 GMT</pubDate><title>Multiple passengers from cruise ship back in U.S.</title><updateDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 23:13:20 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 08 May 2026 00:12:23 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>NBC News&#39; Dr. Akshay Syal breaks down everything you need to know about the hantavirus outbreak that has claimed three lives so far.</description><expires>2056-05-07T22:42:58.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">f_vert_syal_hantavirus_260507</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/video/shorts/what-we-know-about-the-hantavirus-outbreak-so-far-262948421779</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/f_vert_syal_hantavirus_260507/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>What we know about the hantavirus outbreak so far</media:title><media:player url="https://www.nbcnews.com/video/shorts/what-we-know-about-the-hantavirus-outbreak-so-far-262948421779"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/Resize_image_project-znvd5o.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">NBC News&#39; Dr. Akshay Syal breaks down everything you need to know about the hantavirus outbreak that has claimed three lives so far.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/Resize_image_project-znvd5o.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 22:37:47 GMT</pubDate><title>What we know about the hantavirus outbreak so far</title><updateDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 00:12:23 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Ben Kamisar</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 08 May 2026 09:00:00 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Facing a tough election challenge is a cost of doing business for members of Congress.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/redistricting-pits-california-republican-incumbents-fight-survival-rcna343938</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/redistricting-pits-california-republican-incumbents-fight-survival-rcna343938</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260506-Ken-Calvert-Young-Kim-ch-1644-f794d8.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="800" width="1200"><media:credit>Getty Images</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A split composite of Young Kim and Ken Calvert.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Young Kim; Ken Calvert.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260506-Ken-Calvert-Young-Kim-ch-1644-f794d8.jpg" height="800" width="1200"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 09:00:00 GMT</pubDate><title>Redistricting pits California Republican incumbents against each other in a fight for survival</title><updateDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 09:00:00 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Jane C. Timm </dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 07 May 2026 18:25:54 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Tennessee’s Republican-led Legislature passed a new congressional map dividing up the state’s lone majority-Black district, swiftly responding to the U.S.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/tennessee-republicans-pass-map-splitting-states-lone-majority-black-di-rcna343934</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/tennessee-republicans-pass-map-splitting-states-lone-majority-black-di-rcna343934</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-tennessee-capitol-protest-1-ew-317p-7afe18.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Nicole Hester</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Syndication: The Tennessean</media:text><media:description type="plain">Protesters yell as state troopers begin to clear the house gallery under the orders of House Speaker Cameron Sexton on the third day of the special session to redraw congressional maps for Tennessee at the State Capitol in Nashville, Tenn., on May 7, 2026.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-tennessee-capitol-protest-3-ew-317p-7604e5.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1630" width="2500"><media:credit>Nicole Hester</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Syndication: The Tennessean</media:text><media:description type="plain">Democratic representatives walk off the House floor as Republicans pass their redistricting plan.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-tennessee-capitol-protest-2-ew-317p-bc11f2.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Nicole Hester</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Syndication: The Tennessean</media:text><media:description type="plain">Protesters line the halls at the State Capitol.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-tennessee-capitol-protest-4-ew-317p-eb8ce6.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Nicole Hester</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Syndication: The Tennessean</media:text><media:description type="plain">Democratic Rep. Justin Jones walks out of the House chamber and burns a photo of the Confederate flag.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-tennessee-capitol-protest-1-ew-317p-7afe18.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 18:25:54 GMT</pubDate><title>Tennessee Republicans pass map dividing up state’s lone majority-Black district</title><updateDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 23:43:53 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Gary Grumbach </dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 07 May 2026 17:22:37 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The Justice Department is seeking voter registration list data from all 50 states and the District of Columbia over the past year. </description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/justice-department/tracking-dojs-effort-get-us-voter-registration-data-rcna331509</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/justice-department/tracking-dojs-effort-get-us-voter-registration-data-rcna331509</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260413-i-voted-sticker-vl-1214p-56876c.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1210" width="2000"><media:credit>Frederic J. Brown</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Close up on a sheet of &#34;I Voted&#34; stickers being cut on a table</media:text><media:description type="plain">While many states have complied, the Justice Department has sued 30 states and Washington, D.C., for refusing.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260413-i-voted-sticker-vl-1214p-56876c.jpg" height="1210" width="2000"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 17:22:37 GMT</pubDate><title>Tracking the DOJ&#39;s effort to get U.S. voter registration data</title><updateDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 17:22:37 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Suzanne Gamboa</dc:creator><dc:creator>Mike Hixenbaugh</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 07 May 2026 18:34:20 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Daniel Savala, who preached for decades in an Assemblies of God-run college ministry, was sentenced to 30 years in prison without the possibility of parole.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/daniel-savala-christian-missionary-pleads-guilty-abusing-boys-rcna343859</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/daniel-savala-christian-missionary-pleads-guilty-abusing-boys-rcna343859</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-07/250729-daniel-savala-group-cs-7e5e14.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1158" width="1606"><media:credit>Courtesy Olivia Wolf</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Savala poses with Eli Stewart and other young followers in Alaska in 2002.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Savala poses with Eli Stewart and other young followers in Alaska in 2002.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-savala-sentencing-joseph-cleveland-mn-1346-7b99d9.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1200" width="1800"><media:credit>Ilana Panich-Linsman for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Joseph Cleveland stands outside the courthouse before delivering his victim impact statement.</media:text><media:description type="plain">&#34;You thought yourself invincible,&#34; Joseph Cleveland told Daniel Savala while giving an impact statement in court Thursday.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-07/250722-joseph-cleveland-houston-house-mn-1300-7b81ba.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1363" width="2743"><media:credit>Courtesy Joseph Cleveland; Google Maps</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Joseph Cleveland as a young man; Daniel Savala&#39;s house in 2018.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Joseph Cleveland as a teen; Daniel Savala&#39;s house in 2018.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-savala-sentencing-ron-Bloomingkemper-mn-1346-0ddb4b.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1800" width="1440"><media:credit>Ilana Panich-Linsman for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Ron Bloomingkemper</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ron Bloomingkemper Jr., a former Chi Alpha member who for years raised alarm about Savala&#39;s actions, attended his plea hearing.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-savala-sentencing-joseph-cleveland-mn-1345-a2d6e5.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1200" width="1800"><media:credit>Ilana Panich-Linsman for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">From left, Krys Scroggins, Joseph Cleveland, Danny Clark, and far right, Ron Bloomingkemper, listen as Daniel Savala is sentenced.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Former Chi Alpha members, including Joseph Cleveland and Ron Bloomingkemper, listen as Daniel Savala is sentenced. </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-savala-sentencing-joseph-cleveland-mn-1350-357541.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1025" width="1370"><media:credit>Ilana Panich-Linsman for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Joseph Cleveland is embraced after the hearing where he gave an impact statement.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Joseph Cleveland hugs a victim support specialist from the prosecutor&#39;s office after Savala&#39;s guilty plea.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-07/250729-daniel-savala-group-cs-7e5e14.jpg" height="1158" width="1606"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 18:34:20 GMT</pubDate><title>Christian missionary hailed as ‘holiest man alive’ pleads guilty to abusing boys in Texas</title><updateDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 19:57:00 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 08 May 2026 09:44:34 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Alligator appears to knock on Florida front door</description><expires>2056-05-08T09:44:09.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">f_vert_brk_alligator_door_knock_260508</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/video/shorts/alligator-appears-to-knock-on-florida-front-door-262975045621</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencod